properties.name: Aaron
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 4116 n 15th st 68521 lincoln neI\'ve been friends with him sense day one, I can\'t remember a time when he wasn\'t in my life. When we were little it was the stupid things that kept us from just moving on to different friends as we grew up and changed. Things like how we had the same first name, our dads worked in the same place, our cats had the same name, we had the same birthday. 10 years later our cats have both died, our dads no longer work there and we relize that the same birhtday is 4 years apart, yet we are still friends. Now our relationship is based on how we have a lot of the same memories, we have a lot of the same friends, he lives next door to my best friend, and the fact that we have been friends for so long that I don\'t think either one of us would know what to do is we weren\'t. As he gets older I see more and more of his dad in him, especially in his sense of humor. He\'s a awesome guy and somebody that you only run across once in your life so you better sieze the moment.

properties.name: Belmont Elementary school
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 3425 n 14th st 68521 lincoln neThis was the first school I ever attended starting at the age of 7 (I homeschooled before that). It hold a lot of memories for me, good and bad, I hated school at that time. I made a lot of friends there that I still have today. That is the kind of relationship you don\'t want to lose.

properties.name: Brian
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 4801 n 15th st 68521 lincoln neMy favorite Colombian, what can I say I love the kid, in the past few years he has become like a big brother to me. He\'s been there for me through my problems and his. I can always turn to him to make me laugh and give me advice (good and bad). He\'s truely one of a kind!.... :-D

properties.name: Caleb's house
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele  2015 Teton Trail 75077 Lewisville TXMy brother\'s house.

properties.name: Chilton's house
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele  2404 Telluride 75028 Lewisville TXThis is my aunt and uncle house where I spent a lot of my younger years. I still love hanging out there, it is always full of people and activity and a lot of fun. They had 5 kids 3 of which still live at home, soon to be 2 since my oldest cousin recently got engaged.

properties.name: Grandma and Grandpas house
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele215 Alexander rd 68521 Lincoln NEThis is where they have lived ever since I have known them. I have been spending a lot more time there lately, trying to get closer to them because I am scared that my time is limited. Grandma remembers a lot more about the distant past then anything recent. Like she remembers what she did for her 16th birthday but not where grandpa is or what grade I\'m in. She loves to talk about things like that, and what\'s new with the family she can\'t grasp the fact that she now has 3 great grandchildren the youngest of which is named after her. Grandpa is getting old too, but he\'s stuborn as ever (it runs in the family) and he seems to do a better job of taking care of grandma than himself. He also has yet to lose his sense of pride and refuses to ask for help.

properties.name: Joshy
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele   25 Columbia Hts Brooklyn, Ny 11201-2483This is where my cousin Josh is for now. He\'s lived here for the past 7 years and loves it. He now speaks fluent Italian, and is very close to the people that he\'s met there.

properties.name: Lazlo's Brewery and Grill
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele710 p st 68508 lincoln neThis has been a family favorite for o so many years. This is where we go when we go out with a group from the hall, when family is in town it\'s a must, and of course whenever we get those latenight cravings. It also is located in the haymarket (old part of downtown) and seems to have it\'s own personality. You fit in there whether you are dresses to the hills or just off work. Nobody ever looks at you funny, no need to impress anybody here.

properties.name: Lincoln Kingdom Hall of Jehovahs Witnesses
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele3606 n 1st st 68521 lincoln neThis is where I attend now. It is full of my own memories and friends

properties.name: Michelle
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 4108 n 15th 68521 lincoln neMy best friend! We hit it off from word one. I love the girl. She knows more about me than just about anybody and shes still around lol j/k. Shes been there for me through a lot and is a really good friend! She\'s like a sister to me. I couldn\'t do it without her!

properties.name: My current home
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele  711 Benton 68521 Lincoln NEWhere I have lived for way too long, but fortunatly I am moving this summer. It\'s been good to us and holds a lot of awesome memories but I am more than ready to let it go in exchange for our new house. My big sister and brother have moved out so now it\'s just me and my parents here.

This is always a hot spot for something good to eat, something to do, or just a place to chill. It\'s just her and her husband for now, and of course their dog Lucy and cat Jasmine.

properties.name: Seward Kingdom Hall of Jehovahs Witnesses
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele235 river st 68434 seward neThis was the first Kingdom Hall I ever attended, I don\'t remember much about it considering we moved when I was still really little but my family and friends are bursting with memories and old friends.

properties.name: Terrace Grille
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 333 s 13th st 68508 lincoln neThis is my favorite place to eat breakfast. I first discovered it when my sister and brother inlaw took me there one night after a movie. I was about 10 and pretty excited about being in a nice resturante and to top it all of in walks Bill Callahan (the Huskers football coach) with a group of recruites and sat at the table next to us. My brother inlaw being a big fan gote excited and bet me 0 that I couldn\'t get him to talk to me. So the night went on and I couldn\'t get him to make eye contact and I had finally given up since he wouldn\'t look at me and I thought it would be rude to walk up to him. On our way my sister stopped to do something and I sat on the coaches in the lobby with my brother inlaw as soo as we sat down guess who comes walking towards us? Of course, so I jump up and intoduce myself while my brother inlaw almost falls out of his seat laughing so hard. He explained the situation to him and paid up! :-D So that obviously was an amazing first impression (0 is a lot to a little kid). Later on my sister took me there for breakfast and I truely feel in love and it has become somewhat of a tradition. They also have the best hot coco I have ever tasted YUM!

properties.name: The Creamery
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 701 p st 68508 lincoln neThis was where I had my first real ice cream cone. I still go there, and love it. It\'s in the old part of downtown and somehow has managed to maintain the feel it must have had the day it opened. I remember playing in the little corner by the window with all the dools and other toys.

properties.name: The Mill
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele800 p st 68508 lincoln neThe hole in the wall coffe shop that for some reason that only dad can put his finger on everybody loves. We have been going here forever. When I was little they would get me cups of just whip cream, and just the other day about 10 years later my sister ran into a lady who used to work there and knew exactly who my sister was and remembered that she used to bring me in and that they would give me that. WOW! That\'s specail, it might help that we are always in there but still. I love starbucks and all, it\'s great for some things, but you aren\'t getting that there. My loyalty is so to the Mill, there is never snobs, ppl who think that they are better than you, or somebody who isn\'t willing to offer a helping hand there. It really brings the small town fell to the ever growing Lincoln.

properties.name: The blows
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele  725 n 70th 68505 lincoln NEMy only younger cousins, three girls that are so such individuals that have become such a important part of my life in the past few years (along of course with their parents). They are all so different and so great, there are very few people that I will say this about but I am positive that every one of them will grow up to be somebody very special.

properties.name: Vincenzo's Ristorante
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele808 p st 68508 lincoln neThis is my favorite resurante as of last summer. This is also where we (the wedding party) went to before my sisters wedding. It is in historic downtown right next to the coffee shop. They have amazing italian food and usually something that everybody likes. When your done you can take a quick walk down to either the creamery, the movie theater, or the park with the fountain and mural that I think about every family in lincoln has their picture by.

properties.name: air park rec center
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele3720 Nw 46th St, Lincoln, NEK so this place is like the only common thing that is shared by both my childhood, and my big brother and sisters. So many of my most amazing friends wouldn\'t be in my life if it weren\'t for this place. Every Friday in the winter for as long as any of us can remember this place has been the "hot spot" for our group. Whether it be basketball or football or what usually turns into best game of keep away *eVeR* it\'s never dull. Followed by going out to eat, I\'m sure this is the only thing that has kept many of us out of trouble many Friday nights. I will never take forgranted to amazing benefits good friends can bring apon me, this is pretty much the place that holds most of the craziest memories that I wouldn\'t give up for the world.

properties.name: dave matthews band concert
properties.description: Posted by Erinmichele 455 n 10th st 68102 omaha neThis was my first concert. It was amazing, a lot of fun. We ate at Zios pizza in the old market before and made a list of all the songs that we wanted to hear on a napkin. The day after that concert I couldn\'t talk because I was screaming so much the night before.
